0acc32e1509-image.png\" style=\"width: 107px; height: 148px;\" />","<p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/0d8e5dfa-18bc-462c-ba43-e49f5eebe766-image.png\" style=\"width: 96px; height: 138px;\" /></p>"],"answer":2,"solution":"<p><math> <mrow> <mi>N</mi><mi>a</mi><mi>B</mi><msub> <mi>H</mi> <mn>4</mn> </msub> </mrow> </math> is a strong reducing agent as it can reduce carboxylic acids, aldehydes, and ketones. But it cannot reduce double bonds.&nbsp;</p><p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/71a59363-d744-4342-905c-a44c6e685ed9-image.png\" style=\"width: 308px; height: 151px;\" /></p><p>&nbsp;</p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2019 (12 Jan Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":27029,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Aldehydes and Ketones","question":"","options":["<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/4TryUlaY9zzZ8kYzfMTLFwWAIheQ5K5_RrlTWu9YUY0.original.fullsize.png\"/><br/>","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/ov8-kZcA_ilPZJHqmppdExBKSALNY_mGTpLgqd80UlA.original.fullsize.png\"/><br/>","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/waN4peH_CoSOsF3wY58ZsG_7IgX4qRAvkSDaaEH40Qs.original.fullsize.png\"/><br/>","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/n_az6Jl0JoPkx5rvUhffoXRIxQ0kNWcFlPN_sJtflY8.original.fullsize.png\"/><br/>"],"answer":1,"solution":"<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/rdQBB7aZCMbqnQCkqtKFlhcFR2wNnmbOgBD-rCm1YMM.original.fullsize.png\"/><br/>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2025 (7 Apr Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":27170,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Aldehydes and Ketones","question":"","options":["Acetaldehyde","Acetylene","Ethylene","Acetyl chloride"],"answer":2,"solution":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>LiAlH</mi><mn>4</mn></msub></math>&nbsp;is a reducing agent and reduces carboxylic acid to alcohol.&nbsp;</p><p><math> <mrow> <msub> <mtext>CH</mtext> <mn>3</mn> </msub> <mo>COOH</mo> <mover> <mo>&#8594;</mo> <msub> <mtext>LiAlH</mtext> <mn>4</mn> </msub> </mover> <msub> <mtext>CH</mtext> <mn>3</mn> </msub> <mo>-</mo> <msub> <mtext>CH</mtext> <mn>2</mn> </msub> <mo>-</mo> <mtext>OH</mtext> </mrow> </math><br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;(A)<br /><br /><math> <mrow> <mover> <mo>&#8594;</mo> <msub> <mtext>PCl</mtext> <mn>5</mn> </msub> </mover> <msub> <mtext>CH</mtext> <mn>3</mn> </msub> <mo>-</mo> <msub> <mtext>CH</mtext> <mn>2</mn> </msub> <mo>-</mo> <mtext>Cl</mtext> <munderover> <mo>&#8594;</mo> <mtext>KOH</mtext> <mtext>alc</mtext> </munderover> <msub> <mtext>&#160;CH</mtext> <mn>2</mn> </msub> <mo>=</mo> <msub> <mtext>CH</mtext> <mn>2</mn> </msub> </mrow> </math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2014 (06 Apr)","image":null},{"id":27102,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Aldehydes and Ketones","question":"","options":["Both Statement <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">I</mi></math> and Statement <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>II</mi></math> are false.","Both Statement <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">I</mi></math> and Statement <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>II</mi></math> are true.","Statement <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">I</mi></math> is false but Statement <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>II</mi></math> is true.","Statement <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">I</mi></math> is true but Statement <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>II</mi></math> is false."],"answer":3,"solution":"<p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/d1f9e204-a0c8-46f6-a503-afaa579a8659-a24b9a0d-7eb5-4846-931d-bf892d502885-image.png\" style=\"width: 624px; height: 103px;\" /></p><p>The nucleophilic addition of hydrogen cyanide to an aldehyde or a ketone yields cyanohydrin&nbsp;as final product.</p><p><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/66418797-6116-4653-a4e2-cb1a0e076cbd-887bec69-9630-4be3-84fb-7d77edc5f7a6-ss.png\" style=\"width: 655px; height: 182px;\" /></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2021 (01 Sep Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":27182,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Aldehydes and Ketones","question":"","options":["<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/B7UuilfO7sfjir418v8uNStRyaENyUWMJ_fpfUhqQ6I.original.fullsize.png\"><br>","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/ZxnPOOq3sH6Klq9G4UyRBjwNq3BmUrz4gykujp0kJFg.original.fullsize.png\"><br>","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/GqEhzqaeGNSgC0Qb9fBD7XjXyrKMDZRkLsobtAagNLQ.original.fullsize.png\"><br>","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/CalwfPor8aDEGjwBhQvf-SvVGiYPRc8ICP45v1LjZqc.original.fullsize.png\"><br>"],"answer":1,"solution":"Aldehydic group gets oxidised to carboxylic group\nDouble bond breaks and carbon gets oxidised to carboxylic group","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2002","image":null},{"id":27043,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Aldehydes and Ketones","question":"","options":["<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/Jb1i8gPBI3b9RLHtUroOUVQuLMmUyuXxfYpYgS8y-hc.original.fullsize.png\"/><br/>","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/hbvMxpU7opb3i7OsXWyTMe64AG7TsmP8NbzJClrBkYI.original.fullsize.png\"/><br/>","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/Qe6ILN-2w9hM8aAH0e-qOL0ZpN8PKtRMMo0Zi4xShkw.original.fullsize.png\"/><br/>","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/VqN2z68M0Yk-QArfF5QQMjMwVJcvf3AEMDp5dj9_mH4.original.fullsize.png\"/><br/>"],"answer":0,"solution":"This is an example of Tollen's reaction i.e. multiple cross aldol followed by cross Cannizaro reaction\n\n<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/nbyyA0AaK03u0sRW-dYUT7L3n6G6SKARYh7WXFApZZ8.original.fullsize.png\"><br>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2025 (23 Jan Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":27052,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Aldehydes and Ketones","question":"","options":["A","B","C","D"],"answer":0,"solution":"Claisen Schmidt reaction\n<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/904Eet2BXkNsWF2K4wAx5xW0Jz0KCqguPB-dQ3m4Kf8.original.fullsize.png\"><br />mw of benzaldehyde $=106$\n$106 \\times 3=318 \\mathrm{gm}$. Benzaldehyde is required to give 1.5 mole (or $351 \\mathrm{gm}$ ) product","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2024 (05 Apr Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":27085,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Aldehydes and Ketones","question":"","options":["A","B","C","D"],"answer":0,"solution":"<blockquote><p>Aldehydes and ketones undergo reaction with HCN to produce cyanohydrins. The reaction progresses very slowly by using pure hydrogen cyanide. Hence, base as a catalyst helps to speed up the reaction. This is an example of nucleophilic addition reaction.</p><p>here we are given racemic mixture of optically active compound. The attacking nucleophile can attack on carbonyl carbon from either side forming a new chiral carbon. So, in product there will be two chiral carbon but it is symmetrical. So, number of stereoisomers will be 3 only.</p><p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/935d4577-18df-4b04-9f7d-87cf4133bd34-image.png\" style=\"width: 294px; height: 130px;\" /></p></blockquote>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2022 (29 Jul Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":27049,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Aldehydes and Ketones","question":"","options":["(A)-(IV), (B)-(III), (C)-(I), (D)-(II)","(A)-(II), (B)-(III), (C)-(IV), (D)-(I)","(A)-(IV), (B)-(I), (C)-(II), (D)-(III)","(A)-(III), (B)-(I), (C)-(IV), (D)-(II)"],"answer":0,"solution":"(A) Bayer's test $\\rightarrow$ Unsaturation\n(B) Ceric ammonium nitrate test $\\rightarrow$ Alcoholic-OH group\n(C) Phthalein dye test $\\rightarrow$ Phenol\n(D) Schiff's test $\\rightarrow$ Aldehyde","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2024 (08 Apr Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":27162,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Aldehydes and Ketones","question":"","options":["<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/750c7422-0e05-442b-abbb-996ce1c48f64-image.png\" style=\"width: 170px; height: 130px;\" />","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/81a60774-a5d3-4cce-81bb-7b4d057bbcfb-image.png\" style=\"width: 170px; height: 98px;\" />","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/ed6c9975-c407-47f0-a17d-94a5a0e2a378-image.png\" style=\"width: 170px; height: 96px;\" />","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/f8df0ef4-f2a3-4f85-a1f8-7ee297f70c49-image.png\" style=\"width: 170px; height: 129px;\" />"],"answer":0,"solution":"<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>DIBAL</mi><mo>-</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi></math> (diisobutyl aluminium hydride) reduces carboxylic acid and ester to aldehydes.","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2017 (02 Apr)","image":null},{"id":27056,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Aldehydes and Ketones","question":"","options":["A","B","C","D"],"answer":0,"solution":"<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/2xWp7z9IPcbjOoEt5OASgD6bMLM6Ec93VDDHdyKOhxk.original.fullsize.png\"><br>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2024 (04 Apr Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":27163,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Aldehydes and Ketones","question":"","options":["<math><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>3</mn></mrow></msub><mo>-</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi><mo>=</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi><mo>-</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">O</mi></math>","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/39b33271-3e67-490f-aa65-28b8dab68b7d-image.png\" style=\"width: 160px; height: 73px;\" />","<math><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>3</mn></mrow></msub><mo>-</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msub><mo>-</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msub><mo>-</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>3</mn></mrow></msub></math>","<math><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>3</mn></mrow></msub><mo>-</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msub><mo>-</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msub><mo>-</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msub><mo>-</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">O</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi></math>"],"answer":0,"solution":"<p>This reaction is aldol condensation.</p><p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/79164ed3-657f-4956-9ca2-eab5c87f5b48-image.png\" style=\"width: 550px; height: 151px;\" /></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2015 (11 Apr Online)","image":null}]